title: Al Jennings of Oklahoma [1951 - USA] (Dan Duryea) western
description:
Al Jennings of Oklahoma (1951 - USA)

Action / Romance / Western

starring . . . . Dan Duryea, Gale Storm, Dick Foran
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0043272/


The four Jennings brothers are lawyers. When Al's brother is murdered, he goes after the murderer. He outdraws him but a witness says it was murder. Escaping the sheriff he takes refuge on a cattle ranch only to learn all the hands are rustlers. With a price on his head Al joins them and becomes an outlaw and his fame grows as does the reward for his capture. Al Jennings was a real attorney, a real outlaw and later became a politician and an actor in early Western silent films. This movie is reportedly based on his autobiography.
